<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,970,1249]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,970,996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[648,755,970,996]" name="Suriname" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Suriname</collectingCountry>
and is known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[1074,1172,970,996]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">holotype</typeStatus>
(not studied here). The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[247,381,1006,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifera">
<emphasis box="[247,264,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[281,381,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">spinifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a costal bulla on each forewing, probably two small ventromesal processes on segment VII, a pair of long dorsolateral processes on segment IX, and inferior appendages short and not fused to each other (
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[159,281,1078,1104]" firstAuthor="Flint" journalOrPublisher="Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 151" part="14" refId="ref15088" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1974) The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 14, 1 - 151." title="The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint 1974</bibRefCitation>
), being allocated here in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[607,758,1078,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis box="[607,624,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[638,758,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group. However, the male genitalia in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[1206,1337,1078,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinifera">
<emphasis box="[1206,1337,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A. spinifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very distinctive, and can be easily distinguished from those of other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[879,1030,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[879,1030,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Acostatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by segment VIII having an acute median process on the posterior margin in ventral view, by bifid inferior appendages, and by the divided subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
